comments:
In a higher product based on Hyades 3.3, we are analyzing the trace data and 
create analyzed results and hang it off the model (under the same process 
proxy) as a new agent. The process contained in this new agent is subclassed 
from AbstractTRCProcess (and not TRCProcess).

When opening execution statistics view (this could be happening in other places 
too) at monitor/node level, all contained processed are iterated through to 
compute the cumulative time. The process contained in the newly added agent is 
forcefully cast as a TRCProcess, which causes the ClassCastException.

Before doing a cast, a check should be made to make sure it is of the right 
type. These exceptions are thrown even after the view is closed (that could be 
because the trace viewer page for the view is still hanging around and is being 
notified of selections).

Mani, can you extend TRCProcess instead of AbstractTRCProcess ? or are you
trying to avoid any other view to open that process ?

fixed in 3.3 and 4.0 to check process instance to make sure it's instance of
TRCProcess. 
Waiting for Mani's reply on why AbstractTRCProcess is used which may results in
empty TPTP views

We could have subclassed from TRCProcess; but, I guess we wanted to have a real 
lightweight process class, on which we were going to add a whole lot of stuff 
(like leak candidates, path information, ...). It did not make any sense to use 
TRCProcess and populate its values which are not meaningful in the context we 
were using (we would not be able to populate those values at all, since we 
don't have them). 

If we had subclassed from TRCProcess, all the views would have to make 
additional checks to see that there is any data in there.
Mani, Does it mean you are expecting empty value statistic view in your case?

Yes; this agent has no data as for as the statistics view is concerned (even 
the memory stats views). It has its own set of views.
